Adjust rack to top position (top and middle position for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of @salt{for water} water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced). Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Finely chop @chives{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped). Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered).

Toss bell pepper and zucchini on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @oil, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack, ~{7-10%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve 1 1/2 cups pasta cooking water (2 cups for 4 servings), then drain. (Keep empty pot handy for step 5.)

Pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Remove baking sheet from oven; carefully push veggies to one side. Lightly oil empty side of sheet; add salmon, skin sides down. (For 4 servings, leave veggies roasting and lightly oil a second #baking sheet{}; add salmon and roast on middle rack.)

Roast on top rack until salmon is cooked through and veggies are lightly browned and tender, ~{8-10%minutes}.

== Lemon Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in pot used for pasta over medium heat. Add @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp} (2 tsp for 4 servings); cook, stirring, ~{30%seconds}. (Be sure to measure the Italian Seasoning; we sent more.)

Whisk in @cheese roux concentrate{1%ounce} and 1 cup reserved pasta cooking water (1 1/2 cups for 4). Cook, whisking, until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Reduce heat to medium low and whisk in @cream cheese{2%tablespoon} until smooth.

== Assembly ==

Add drained penne, @peas{4%ounce}, half the @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} (save the rest for serving), half the lemon zest, @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), and a big squeeze of lemon juice to pot with sauce. Cook, stirring, until butter has melted and pasta is coated in a creamy sauce.

> If needed, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time.

Stir in roasted veggies. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add more lemon zest or lemon juice if you like.

> For an extra-rich experience, stir in 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4).

== To Serve ==

Divide pasta between #plates{}. Top with salmon, chives, and remaining Parmesan. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.